1
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:41,009
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:43,950
[Episode 30]

3
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:14,360
Actually, I'm quite afraid
you'll regret coming to Hong Kong with me.

4
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,210
Why?

5
00:02:15,830 --> 00:02:18,160
I'm afraid you were just being impulsive.

6
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:20,150
I was just being impulsive.

7
00:02:25,730 --> 00:02:27,410
So sometimes acting on impulse

8
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:29,300
doesn't seem like a bad thing.

9
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:31,890
What do you mean?

10
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,690
Are you not happy today?

11
00:02:34,670 --> 00:02:35,670
I am happy.

12
00:02:36,510 --> 00:02:39,060
And I haven't been
this happy in a long time.

13
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,070
Really?

14
00:02:43,190 --> 00:02:44,840
And I feel like today

15
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:47,940
you're a bit different from usual.

16
00:02:52,770 --> 00:02:54,050
Is that good or bad?

17
00:02:54,990 --> 00:02:55,870
Take a guess.

18
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:03,910
Every side of you is so attractive to me.

19
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:45,360
I'm sorry.

20
00:03:48,170 --> 00:03:49,900
I'm the one who should be sorry.

21
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:18,380
I thought I could just let loose for a bit

22
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:20,230
and treat this trip

23
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:22,180
as a reward for myself,

24
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,920
relying on my most instinctual impulses

25
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,630
to accept the man beside me.

26
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,360
But it wasn't until I pushed him away

27
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,360
that I realized

28
00:04:30,970 --> 00:04:32,830
no matter how much I try to escape,

29
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:34,880
I can't deceive myself.

30
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,830
Good morning, everyone.

31
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,360
Ms. Xu.

32
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,190
How was it? Was Hong Kong fun?

33
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,270
Is that even a question?

34
00:05:02,270 --> 00:05:04,190
Just look at Ms. Xu today.

35
00:05:04,190 --> 00:05:06,240
The trip to Hong Kong
was definitely worth it.

36
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,190
Could you two stop gossiping so much?

37
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:08,820
Right.

38
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:11,280
Someone just sent over
two invitation letters.

39
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,230
One is for you,

40
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,720
and the other is for Mr. Ji.

41
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:16,180
It seems there's some kind of event.

42
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,260
[I Sincerely Invite You to a Unique]

43
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:17,400
[Jazz-Themed Gathering, By Marcos Yang]

44
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:18,430
Ms. Xu.

45
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:20,750
If you are going to see Mr. Ji later,

46
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:22,580
could you bring this to him for me?

47
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:24,070
I will not be seeing Mr. Ji later.

48
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:25,390
Tell him to come get it himself.

49
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:28,190
-Okay.
-Ms. Xu, you're needed in the banquet hall.

50
00:05:28,790 --> 00:05:30,390
Okay, I'm coming right away.

51
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:31,750
Mr. Ji.

52
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:34,670
Good morning.

53
00:05:38,030 --> 00:05:38,870
Mr. Ji,

54
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,700
someone just brought you
this invitation letter.

55
00:05:41,850 --> 00:05:42,920
Okay. I got it.

56
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:58,490
Marcos said
it's a private gathering of his.

57
00:05:58,620 --> 00:06:00,350
He hopes to thank you in person.

58
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,250
I will go.

59
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:09,410
I heard you went to
Hong Kong these past few days.

60
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:11,900
Did it rain there?

61
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,390
No.

62
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,060
Then the weather forecast was wrong.

63
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,940
It's good that it didn't rain.

64
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:28,150
You just recovered.

65
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,750
Be careful not to catch a cold again.

66
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:52,420
Mr. Peng! Mr. Peng!

67
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:53,430
Wait!

68
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,060
Please give us another chance.

69
00:06:56,060 --> 00:06:56,950
Mr. Peng!

70
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:00,880
Mr. Peng!

71
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,070
Why didn't you stop

72
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:13,960
such an important client from leaving?

73
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,110
I'm sorry, Mr. Duan.

74
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:15,870
I...

75
00:07:16,450 --> 00:07:17,040
Get lost.

76
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,090
I don't want to see you again.

77
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:18,980
I'm sorry.

78
00:07:47,190 --> 00:07:48,080
Mr. Duan Jr.

79
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,040
I didn't expect

80
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:58,530
you'd look pretty cool
riding a motorcycle.

81
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,610
There's a lot you'd never expect.

82
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,620
Are we going or not?

83
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:04,070
Where to?

84
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,820
I'm really popular right now.

85
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:08,820
It'll be troublesome
if I get recognized when I go out.

86
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:10,050
Going for a motorcycle ride.

87
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:11,110
Want to come along?

88
00:08:11,690 --> 00:08:12,500
Wait.

89
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,430
Why are you suddenly so attentive today?

90
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:16,600
Is it that guy Ji Feng

91
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,930
who sent you to spy on me?

92
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,020
You're so slow and naggy.

93
00:08:25,020 --> 00:08:26,080
Hurry up and get on.

94
00:08:27,730 --> 00:08:30,540
Since you begged me
so much to accompany you,

95
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:33,090
I'll reluctantly go with you.

96
00:08:55,650 --> 00:08:58,390
How is it? Feeling better?

97
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,200
Who said I was in a bad mood?

98
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,640
Don't overthink it.

99
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:05,000
Fine, I'm the one in a bad mood, okay?

100
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:10,740
Pull over.

101
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:12,750
What's wrong?

102
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,590
Stop! I'm going to throw up.

103
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:17,120
Don't throw up.

104
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,740
Don't throw up in my helmet.

105
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:37,280
Why didn't you tell me
you get motion sickness earlier?

106
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:39,870
Don't tell anyone.

107
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:43,660
I have leverage over you now.

108
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,320
Why is it that every time

109
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,720
I encounter such a mess

110
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,790
I bump into you?

111
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,960
Is this considered fate?

112
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:00,710
What are you trying to say?

113
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,630
I'm trying to say...

114
00:10:04,330 --> 00:10:06,420
Should I take over a barbecue place?

115
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:10,580
The big star is taking
a down-to-earth route?

116
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,810
What do you know?

117
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,240
This is called investing in my hobbies.

118
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,770
Since this didn't work out,

119
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:18,020
maybe I'll have better luck
with the barbecue place

120
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:19,180
and make it big?

121
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:22,410
Then I'll let you be my Chef.

122
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:24,490
You... you just grill

123
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:26,270
those things you grilled

124
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:28,670
at the party last time.

125
00:10:29,910 --> 00:10:31,240
What makes you think

126
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:34,120
I would give up being
a Chef at a five-star hotel

127
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,390
to work at your barbecue stand?

128
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:38,050
I'm personally inviting you.

129
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,180
Isn't that enough?

130
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,670
At worst,

131
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,790
I'll give you the naming rights

132
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:44,620
to the barbecue restaurant.

133
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:46,750
You can name it whatever you want then.

134
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:49,640
Like Chef Qiao,

135
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:52,670
or Qiaoqi's Selection.

136
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:53,840
Duan Aoxiang,

137
00:10:53,860 --> 00:10:55,570
are you trying to hit on me?

138
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:03,790
What if I say yes?

139
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,680
How would you answer?

140
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:10,230
It depends on my mood.

141
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,730
What does that mean?

142
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:15,910
It means

143
00:11:16,210 --> 00:11:17,860
it depends on my mood.

144
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,430
I'm leaving.

145
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,240
Kenny.

146
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,760
Over here.

147
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:57,150
Marcos.

148
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:58,550
Thank you for coming.

149
00:11:58,580 --> 00:11:59,700
Come here.

150
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:01,870
Everyone,

151
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:03,490
this is my very good friend.

152
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:05,750
A famous hotel manager.

153
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:09,370
Ji Feng, general manager of Purong Hotel.

154
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:11,000
Nice to meet you.

155
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:11,960
Marcos.

156
00:12:11,990 --> 00:12:13,630
Do you also cooperate with Purong Hotel?

157
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:14,500
Of course.

158
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,760
Purong's service is extremely thoughtful.

159
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:19,090
And after we established
our cooperation back then,

160
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:21,330
I found that Kenny and I
got along really well.

161
00:12:21,330 --> 00:12:22,740
Marcos really gives us a lot of face,

162
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:25,580
generously promoting our Purong Hotel.

163
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,160
It's my pleasure.

164
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,730
We are a bit flattered.

165
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,720
Where is Ms. Xu?

166
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:32,730
I forgot to tell you.

167
00:12:32,770 --> 00:12:34,320
She is the lobby manager now,

168
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,430
and has to handle many things herself.

169
00:12:36,430 --> 00:12:38,370
She's probably tied up with hotel matters.

170
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:39,180
Okay.

171
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:43,920
Ms. Xu.

172
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:07,720
Ms. Xu.

173
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,710
Long time no see, Mr. Yang.

174
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:11,500
You look

175
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,500
so beautiful today.

176
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:14,550
Thank you.

177
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:16,370
I should be the one thanking you.

178
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:17,910
My grandfather has now remembered

179
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:19,220
many things from the past.

180
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:21,570
His condition has improved a lot.

181
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:22,390
Most importantly,

182
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:24,840
he is now willing to share with me

183
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,510
the stories from his youth

184
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:27,790
when he was in China.

185
00:13:28,730 --> 00:13:30,780
This is all thanks to you.

186
00:13:31,330 --> 00:13:32,520
That's wonderful.

187
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:33,710
Congratulations.

188
00:13:34,570 --> 00:13:35,360
Thank you.

189
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:40,030
By the way, I just heard Kenny say

190
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:42,870
that you've been
promoted to lobby manager.

191
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,270
Congratulations.

192
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:44,870
Thank you.

193
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:46,720
I knew Kenny

194
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:49,070
would never overlook a talent like you.

195
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:51,930
It's because Ms. Xu
has outstanding abilities,

196
00:13:51,970 --> 00:13:54,260
and Purong Hotel is
exactly in need of talent.

197
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,440
You know, Marcos,

198
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:57,270
for both employees and the company,

199
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:58,900
they need to help each other succeed.

200
00:13:58,900 --> 00:13:59,870
That's true.

201
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:03,200
Then let me congratulate the two of you.

202
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,120
Come on, cheers.

203
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,150
Thank you.

204
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:09,030
By the way,

205
00:14:09,090 --> 00:14:11,680
how about I introduce
some friends from our side?

206
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:12,320
Sure.

207
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:13,220
Come, let's go.

208
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:16,960
Hello.

209
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,320
These two are my friends,

210
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,790
Miyu and Ji Feng.

211
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,310
They are both from Purong Hotel.

212
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:22,410
Nice to meet you.

213
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,820
You can come if you have a holiday.

214
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:31,440
Nice to meet you.

215
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:33,600
This is Miyu and Ji Feng.

216
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:34,320
They are both my friends.

217
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,640
Miyu, Ji Feng.

218
00:14:35,930 --> 00:14:36,860
Nice to meet you.

219
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,740
How is the party today?

220
00:14:42,210 --> 00:14:43,170
It is okay?

221
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,080
Not bad.

222
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,150
Is the AC too strong?

223
00:14:46,180 --> 00:14:47,060
It's a bit cold.

224
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:48,660
I'm going to the restroom.

225
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:49,860
Don't drink too much.

226
00:14:53,590 --> 00:14:55,720
There's food over there too.

227
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:57,190
You can go and have some.

228
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:03,840
[Tan Jizhou]

229
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,170
Miyu, I've arrived in Shanghai.

230
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,390
Can we meet?

231
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:17,120
Kenny.

232
00:15:17,470 --> 00:15:18,060
What's up?

233
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:19,590
I want to ask you a question.

234
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:23,100
Do you like Ms. Xu?

235
00:15:24,570 --> 00:15:26,300
Why do you think so?

236
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:28,740
I saw you looking at her all night.

237
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:31,330
Your eyes hardly left her.

238
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,570
It's quite obvious.

239
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:34,470
Marcos.

240
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:35,800
Yeah.

241
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:36,670
I do like her.

242
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:38,210
Is there a problem?

243
00:15:44,430 --> 00:15:46,550
If you like her, tell her.

244
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:48,230
Let her know how you feel.

245
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:49,100
Right?

246
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,180
How about this?

247
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:53,120
There's a dance session coming up.

248
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:55,130
Take this chance to ask her out.

249
00:15:57,180 --> 00:15:58,020
Give it a try.

250
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,330
Excuse me.

251
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,450
Are you here alone?

252
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:20,300
No.

253
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,130
Then,

254
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:24,110
where is your partner?

255
00:16:24,370 --> 00:16:25,830
How could he have the heart to

256
00:16:25,830 --> 00:16:27,620
leave someone as beautiful as you alone?

257
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,150
Is there anything you need?

258
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,380
The dancing is about to start.

259
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:35,140
I'd like to ask you for a dance.

260
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,450
I'm afraid I'm not available.

261
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:38,380
Please find someone else, thanks.

262
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:39,740
Miss.

263
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,290
Excuse me.

264
00:16:46,690 --> 00:16:48,150
She already has a partner.

265
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,240
Sorry.

266
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:58,740
Thank you.

267
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:00,140
It's nothing.

268
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:11,200
Are you okay?

269
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:13,780
I'm fine.

270
00:17:32,060 --> 00:17:33,390
Why aren't you dancing?

271
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,490
Do you want to?

272
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:12,450
After this,

273
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:13,840
what are your plans?

274
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,450
What's wrong? Something up at the hotel?

275
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,360
I want to ask you out.

276
00:18:22,390 --> 00:18:24,050
Stop saying things like that.

277
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,780
Then do you

278
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,580
have a date with someone else?

279
00:18:28,730 --> 00:18:30,200
Mr. Ji, you're drunk.

280
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,150
Maybe.

281
00:18:43,550 --> 00:18:44,640
Mrs. Nie.

282
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:51,740
What's so strange about this?

283
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:54,160
When the husband
has a little affair or two,

284
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,510
you just turn a blind eye

285
00:18:55,510 --> 00:18:56,440
and let it pass.

286
00:18:56,690 --> 00:18:59,400
Nie Yucheng is the one
making money to support their family.

287
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,290
What could she possibly complain about?

288
